13/08/2009
ATHENS, Greece -- The justice ministry announced on Wednesday (August 12th) that Germany will extradite former Siemens manager Michael Christoforakos to Greece, where he faces charges of bribery and money laundering. 
A court in Munich ordered the extradition. 
Christoforakos, who holds dual Greek and German citizenship, was arrested in Germany on June 25th based on an arrest warrant issued by Greece. 
He allegedly offered bribes to employees of the Hellenic Telecommunications Organisation while employed by Siemens. 
(ANA-MPA, Bloomberg, Forbes - 12/08/09)
